         <abstract>
            <p>Let p ≠ 1 be a positive real number. We determine all real numbers α = α(p) and β = β(p) such that the inequalities &lt;latex&gt;$\lbrack 1 - e^{-\beta x^p}\rbrack^{1/p} &lt; \frac{1}{\Gamma(1 + 1/p)} \int^x_0 e^{-t^p} dt &lt; \lbrack 1 - e^{-\alpha x^p}\rbrack^{1/p}$&lt;/latex&gt; are valid for all &lt;latex&gt;$x &gt; 0$&lt;/latex&gt;. And, we determine all real numbers a and b such that -log(1 - e&lt;sup&gt;-ax&lt;/sup&gt;) ≤ ∫&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;x&lt;/sub&gt; e&lt;sup&gt;-t&lt;/sup&gt;/t dt ≤ -log(1 - e&lt;sup&gt;-bx&lt;/sup&gt;) hold for all &lt;latex&gt;$x &gt; 0$&lt;/latex&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
